	(173,9,9,6,1,'10','Week 5','2','2','100 min.','Describe Leisure Activities.\r\n\r\nTalk about frequency.','Leisure activities.','Every day activities','Students will learn to describe some of the leisure activities that they enjoy doing alone, with friends or with their families.\r\n\r\nThey will use the adverbs of frequency (Always, Usually,Often, Sometimes/Seldom, Rarely/Hardly ever and Never) to express the frequency in which they do a particular activity.','Warm up ','How often do you exercise? \r\n\r\nHow often do you go out with friends?\r\n\r\nHow often do you watch movies with your family?','Students are able to describe the frequency in which they do activities.','Answer correctly to questions about   the the frequency in which they do activities as well the frequency a member of their family does an activity.','Students are able to write sentences and talk using the adverbs of frequency.','No se requería','Students share what they learn about the adverbs of frequency.','Activities done in their book.\r\n\r\nOral activity sharing their feelings about the adverbs of frequency.','Title: Upload Us 1\r\n\r\nDescription:Student Book & Workbook\r\n\r\nISBN: 978-1-84862-800-7\r\nLevel: Beginner\r\n\r\nAuthors:Virginia Evans & Jenny Dooley ','E-Book\r\n\r\n','Whiteboard, Markers, Projector, Laptop, English E- Book software, Laser.','complete the chart on page 41 from their books.',4,'2012-10-26 11:14:48'),
	(174,9,9,6,1,'11','Week 6','2','2','100 min.','Interview a person.\r\n\r\nRead for specific information.','Means of transportation.','Every day activities','Students will learn to formulate questions to do an interview.\r\n\r\nThey will use the simple present (Wh-questions) Intonation.','Warm up ','Have you ever done an interview?\r\n\r\nHave you been interviewed?\r\n\r\nHow did you feel?','Students are able to make a good interview by formulating good questions.','Answer correctly to questions in an interview.','Students are able to write sentences and questions that later on they will use to make an interview.','No se requería','Students share what questions have they formulated to make during the interview.','Activities done in their book.\r\n\r\nWritten activity with the questions formulated for the interview.\r\n','Title: Upload Us 1\r\n\r\nDescription:Student Book & Workbook\r\n\r\nISBN: 978-1-84862-800-7\r\nLevel: Beginner\r\n\r\nAuthors:Virginia Evans & Jenny Dooley ','E-Book\r\n\r\n','Whiteboard, Markers, Projector, Laptop, English E- Book software, Laser.','Find someone in your family and with your friends and make an interview, write down his or her answers, save the questions and the answers in your portfolio.',4,'2012-10-26 11:51:30'),
	(175,9,9,6,1,'12','Week 6','2','2','100 min.','Invite/Accept - Decline.\r\n\r\nReading: are you a couch potato?','Places to go & activities.','Every day activities','Students will learn to formulate invitations to do activities, they will also learn how to accept or decline an invitation.\r\n\r\nThey will use the prepositions of time (at, on, in).','Warm up ','Do you want to go to the movies tonight?\r\n\r\nWould you like to have lunch today?\r\n\r\nCould you come with me tonight?','Students are able to invite whomever they like to do a particular activity.','Students accept or decline invitations to do activities in a proper  manner.','Students are able to speak and write invitations as well to accept or decline them.','No se requería','Students think about an invitation that they could make to one of their friends.','Activities done in their book.\r\n\r\n\r\n','Title: Upload Us 1\r\n\r\nDescription:Student Book & Workbook\r\n\r\nISBN: 978-1-84862-800-7\r\nLevel: Beginner\r\n\r\nAuthors:Virginia Evans & Jenny Dooley ','E-Book\r\n\r\n','Whiteboard, Markers, Projector, Laptop, English E- Book software, Laser.','N/A',4,'2012-10-26 12:01:09'),
